Parliament, Monday, 28 October 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Sports, Arts and Culture will receive a briefing from the Department of Arts and Culture on the missing R100 million in the Mzansi Golden Economy project. The committee will also receive a briefing from the Moral Regeneration Movement on its annual report. Venue: S35, First Floor, NCOP Building
	Time: 09:30 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON SPORTS, ARTS AND CULTURE, MS BEAUTY DLULANE. For media inquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Sibongile Maputi (Mr)
